  "most_recent_game": {
    "date": "2026-03-14",
    "opponent": "Fiu",
    "result": "W",
    "boxscore_url": "https://www.wkusports.com/sports/baseball/stats/2026/fiu/boxscore/13278",
    "recap_url": "https://www.wkusports.com/news/2026/3/14/baseball-hilltoppers-walk-off-fiu-in-10-innings-to-clinch-series",
    "recap_headline": "Western Kentucky University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BOWLING GREEN, Ky. -\nWKU Baseball (11-8, 2-0 CUSA) defeated FIU (7-13, 0-2 CUSA) 5-4 in 10 innings Saturday afternoon at Nick Denes Field.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nFIU got on the board first with a pair of hits, the last plating the runner from first base. With a runner on third a groundball to\nJP Acosta\nwas gloved but the runner scored from third to put the Panthers up 2-0.\nIn the top of third the Panthers put runners on first and second but\nAaron Robertson\nforced a pop fly to the shortstop and recorded his first strikeout to end the threat.\nIn the bottom of the frame,\nAustin Haller\nlaced his second single of the afternoon and\nCamden Ross\nand\nLane Arroyos\neach followed with four-pitch walks to load the bases with no outs.\nKyle Hayes\nthen knocked one through the left side for his sixth RBI of the weekend to put the Hilltoppers on the board.\nDaniel Stewart\ngrounded into a double-play but scored Ross from third to even the score at two apiece.\nFavela came in in the fourth and struck out his first two batters. The Panthers attempted their second steal but were denied for the second time by Ross to end the top half of the frame.\nIn the top of the fifth FIU managed a walk and took a two-run lead with a home run into the right field bullpen.\nIn the bottom half, Ross roped a ball into left center field and ended up at second with a standup double. Arroyos then drove him in with another double into the left field corner to make it a one run game.\nIn the top of the sixth FIU put their first two batters on base with runners on first and second with no outs. Favela then recorded a strikeout and a flyout then\nSam Frizzi\ncame in and recorded the last out with a strikeout.\nHaller walked to lead off the seventh and Ross got aboard with a single into right field. Arroyos connected on a 1-0 pitch into right center field that scored Haller for an RBI double and a tie game at 4-4.\nNathan Lawson\nentered to pitch for WKU in the eighth and after a one out base hit, Lawson recorded two strikeouts to end the top half of the inning.\nIn the bottom of the 10th Hayes walked and Acosta was intentionally walked with one out to put runners on first and second. After a flyout,\nManny Alberto\ncame to the dish and a 2-1 count lifted one into left center field to score\nKiefer Tarnoki\nfrom second and give WKU its second walk-off win in 2026.\nNOTABLES\nWith the win WKU improves to 11-8 (2-0 CUSA) on the year and 11-7 at Nick Denes Field.\nAaron Robertson\ngot the starting nod for the Hilltoppers on Saturday afternoon. He would finish with two earned runs on five hits in 3.0 innings of work.\nWKU used four relievers on Saturday in\nJude Favela\n,\nSam Frizzi\n,\nDawson Hall\n, and\nNathan Lawson\n.\nLawson was credited with the win, throwing the final 3.0 innings and allowing just two hits, one walk, and two strikeouts in 13 batters faced.\nThe win marks the second this season for Lawson who is now 2-0.\nManny Alberto\nled the Hilltoppers going 2-for-5 with one RBI and a stolen base. His five at-bats were a season high.\nAlberto had the game winning walk-off RBI base hit in the bottom of the 10th inning to clinch the series for the Hilltoppers.\nAlberto's two hits marked a career high as a Hilltopper.\nHis game-winning RBI was also the first for the redshirt-junior in a Hilltopper uniform.\nLane Arroyos\nwent 2-for-4 and knocked two RBIs to lead WKU in that front on Saturday.\nAustin Haller\nwent 2-for-4, reaching on his first two plate appearances and scoring two runs, one being the game-tying run in the seventh inning.\nCamden Ross\nwent 2-for-3 with two hits and two runs on Saturday.\nRoss also threw out two on the base paths on Saturday, matching a career high. The last being on May 3, 2024 at UNC Asheville.\nWith the win WKU moves to 2-0 in CUSA play, marking the first time the Hilltoppers have started 2-0 in league play since 2019.\nWKU's last walk-off win prior to Saturday night was a 9-8 win in nine innings over LA Tech on May 3, 2025.\nQUOTABLE\nOn the win, head coach Marc Rardin said \"Care is important for us. There're 42 guys in that dugout and you can't tell who is on the active roster for the weekend and who isn't. That's being unselfish and having a care, more importantly than for the program but for each other and they're excited for each other. That strength and that care goes a long way.\"\nNEXT UP\nThe Hilltoppers will wrap up the CUSA opening series with FIU on Sunday, March 15. First pitch is set for 12 p.m. Tickets for the game can be purchased\nHERE.\nHow to follow WKU Baseball:\nFor complete information on WKU Hilltopper Baseball, visit WKUSports.com or follow the program via social media @WKU_Baseball on X and @WKUBaseball on Instagram."
  },
